{"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One of the quickest ways you can erode my trust is by asking me to sign something at the wrong time. Like an NDA before you discuss a project with me or a contract in a situation where a friendly handshake would do."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"My policy is when in doubt, trust. You trusting me will make me trust you more. A positive cycle."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"date: 2015-06-02T22:41:58-05:00"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/06-02-building-trust-by-giving-trust"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","metadata":{"title":"Building Trust by Giving Trust","platforms":[{"name":"Brunow","introducedAt":"2017.01.20"}],"modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"}},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2015"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/06-02-building-trust-by-giving-trust"},"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/archive","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Archive","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"All posts"}]},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"type":"topic","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he."}],"title":"Brunow